            Management structure



Management structure

We believe that doing the right thing for our clients is our most important responsibility. We are committed to delivering high standards of governance and to remaining relevant and competitive for all our clients.







HSBC Global Asset Management is wholly owned by HSBC Holdings plc (HSBC Group), one of the largest financial services organisations in the world.
The Board of HSBC Global Asset Management, chaired by an independent non-executive director, endorses the annual operating plan and receives reports from HSBC Global Asset Management’s Risk Management Committee.
The Global Executive Committee provides business oversight, monitoring and stewardship for the business and drives business development, sales and distribution, giving due consideration to local board and corporate management requirements.

Global Executive Committee
Our Global Executive Committee, which is based in London, sets the strategic direction for HSBC Global Asset Management. It focuses on major operating policies and comprises a small group of senior executives with global functional responsibilities.



